comments: I loved her and her class. This class had the potential to be boring but she really made it interesting! Go to class for sure but it is always fun so its cool. She never gives 100\'s but her grading isnt too hard. Love her and her class so TAKE HER! She is so funny!!!!

She made class so much fun! Pay close attention. Her papers are easy, she posts prompts before hand. Her tests are like her notes if you take good notes you will be fine overall I would say take her! Because she is Awesome!!!

She is by FAR my favorite professor at FSU. She keeps a regularly boring class, interesting. You do have to go to class to do well, but it\'s worth it. She is understanding and fun, her only downfall is she doesn\'t give 100\'s but I wouldn\'t say her grading is harsh. You just have to work for it.
Good lectures. Does not ever give 100%, she is picky. The tests are very detailed. Take good notes.. if you decide to take her.

Her class is kind of difficult, but if you attend and take good notes you should be fine. She\'s HILARIOUS! I look forward to this class becaus she makes it fun and interesting. I would take her again if she taught more classes. I recommend her to everyone looking for a good history class!
She is super funny and i always wanted to go to her class. I wish every prof i had was as good as her. And she\'s really pretty.TAKE HER!
I looked forward to class. She was funny as hell. Textsbooks were too expensive though and they don\'t help you study, you have to go to class
She is amazing! She teaches like a giant story and its really easy to follow along! you need to go to class and take good notes because she wants details on exams but she is so good!

Please do not take this teacher. No matter how much you study it is hard to get a satisfactory grade. True she offers extra credit and such, but it does not help. For your sanity please consider taking another professor.

AMAZING TEACHER! she is a great lecturer, she teaches like she is telling one giant story which makes it easy to follow along and remember. Take good notes because her exams are detailed. She is very specific with what she wants but is very good with her office hours. Her essay assignments aren\'t bad and she will read over your drafts. TAKE HER!

I enjoy her class, but her tests are ridiculous and her assignments are graded extremely harshly. Her tests are on very specific material that are barely mentioned in class. Her assignments are reasonably challenging, but she grades them like a b#!*h. I am amazing at writing papers and all that, and she never gave me full credit for anything.
She is a grad student who thinks this is a 5000 level class. It is race and immigration.. She grades harder than any teacher I have had and the class average was a C-. Great teacher :/
Was my worst grade at FSU and I am graduating. I studied all the notes and read the book just as much as any other class. She grades like race and ethnicity is your major. I do not like her at all

We are only a month into class and she is my favorite teacher so far at FSU. She appeals to all learning types by showing clips and is really funny and makes learning fun. She reviews what we learned in the previous class. Make sure to take notes she doesn\'t post it but she makes going to class fun. DO TAKE HER CLASS!
